==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Murderer
<hw>Mur"der*er</hw> <pr>(m⟦ucir⟧r"d⟦etil⟧r*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One guilty of murder; a person who, in possession of
his reason, unlawfully kills a human being with premeditated
malice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small cannon, formerly used for clearing a ship's
decks of boarders; -- called also <altname>murdering
piece</altname>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Murderess</ent>⟦br⟧
